{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "/second-brain-wiki Wiki this:\n\n# Vector Similarity Search\n\nUsing vector embeddings to find semantically similar content.\nCore technique behind modern search and recommendation systems.\n\n- Transforms text into embeddings via transformer models\n- Compares vectors using cosine similarity or dot product\n- Approximate algorithms (HNSW, IVF) trade accuracy for speed\n- Powers RAG retrieval, recommendation engines, deduplication"}, "timestamp": "2026-07-09T15:56:18.692Z"}
