tics-jagged-edge.md, evaluator-super-agent.md\n- Category: Meetings\n\n## 2026-06-16 — Updated: My Cursor Claw (Week 4 growth)\n\n**Updated:** my-cursor-claw.md — expanded from 12 to 20+ skills, added 5th MCP (Slack), added Automated Daily Review System section documenting the 3-checkpoint launchd infrastructure (morning/midday/EOD with Apple Reminders, progress doc auto-update).\n\n**New skills documented:** second-brain-ingest, work-context, meeting-prep, standup-writer, session-log, sprint-manager, critique, doc-sync, humanize-text, superpowers, skill-guide.\n\n**Index updated:** My Cursor Claw entry updated to reflect current scope.\n\n## 2026-06-09 — Initial wiki seeding\n\n**Sources ingested:**\n- sources/2026-06-09-prototype-creator-overview.html\n- sources/2026-06-03-nielsen-agents-task1.html\n- sources/2026-06-04-agent-eval-harness-overview.html\n- sources/2026-06-05-skill-eval-cheat-sheet.html\n- Andy/Evan meeting notes (2026-06-08, Google Drive)\n- jnemargut/decision-kit README (GitHub)\n- opendatahub-io/rfe-creator README (GitHub)\n- andybraren/prototype-creator README + CLAUDE.md (GitHub)\n\n**Pages created (9):**\n- prototype-creator.md — Phase 2 of AI-SDLC, prototype generation pipeline\n- ai-sdlc-pipeline.md — three-phase pipeline overview (rfe → prototype → strat)\n- decision-kit.md — Decision Driven Development toolkit, 24 skills\n- agent-eval-harness.md — skill quality evaluation framework\n- nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md — first internship task, AI model comparison\n- my-cursor-claw.md — personal workspace with 12 skills and 4 MCP connections\n- ux-quality-rubric.md — 4-dimension prototype scoring system\n- evaluator-super-agent.md — upcoming assignment, automated prototype evaluation\n- rfe-creator.md — Phase 1 of AI-SDLC, RFE creation and assessment\n\n**Cross-links established:** All 9 pages interlinked based on topical relationships. Key connections: prototype-creator ↔ decision-kit (integration), evaluator-super-agent ↔ agent-eval-harness (pattern reuse), nielsens-heuristics ↔ evaluator-super-agent (methodology).\n\n**Index updated:** 3 categories created (Red Hat AI-SDLC, Evaluation & Quality, Tools & Skills).\n\n## 2026-06-09 — Ingested: Prototype Creator Demo Transcript (May 14)\n\n**Source:** sources/2026-05-14-prototype-creator-demo-transcript.md — ~2 hour recorded walkthrough by Andy Braren with Beau Morley and Dash Copeland\n\n**Created:** prototype-creator-demo-may14.md — Comprehensive summary covering both automated/speedrun and human-in-the-loop workflows, git submodule integration, preview URLs, token usage, and extensive team discussion on designer workflow, outcome-level prototyping, and the vision for tools beyond Cursor.\n\n**Cross-linked with:** prototype-creator.md (added demo reference), evaluator-super-agent.md (added \"Key Design Inputs from Demo\" section with 5 actionable insights: scope to NEW elements, generate decision pages in auto mode, outcome-level awareness, preview URL as eval entry point, token efficiency)\n\n**Category:** Red Hat AI-SDLC\n\n## 2026-06-09 — Ingested: Proposal for an Outcome Tiger Team\n\n**Source:** sources/2026-06-09-outcome-tiger-team-proposal.pdf — Andy Braren's proposal for agentic outcome creation, prioritization, and visualization. 3 workstreams: outcome creation, E2E prototype validation, outcome prioritization aid (\"Leaderboard of Pain\").\n\n**Created:** outcome-tiger-team.md — Comprehensive summary covering the problem (RFEs/STRATs disconnected from outcomes), three workstreams mapped to benefits, pipeline extension diagram, and direct connections to the evaluator super agent's outcome-level awareness requirement.\n\n**Cross-linked with:** ai-sdlc-pipeline.md (added outcomes as upstream step in flow diagram), prototype-creator.md (added Workstream 2 E2E validation link), evaluator-super-agent.md (added outcome-level awareness connection), rfe-creator.md (added Workstream 1 pattern reuse link)\n\n**Category:** Red Hat AI-SDLC\n\n## 2026-06